6.37pm What a stunning opening salvo to the Ashes. Australia were dead and buried at 122 for 8 ... but Smith found resolute support from Peter Siddle and Nathan Lyon, to climb back onto the offensive with an outstanding 144 from 219 balls. Australia's 284 is worth nearer 450 given their back story. And there will be about ten six minutes for their day to get even better against England's ropey top order ... don't go away!
